* Workflow expected `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`, actual is `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n- **Spinner dependency uncertainty.** Architecture says spinner, 14-1 chose static `◆`. Story instructs dev to check for ink-spinner first.\n- **No UX spec coverage.** All requirements from PRD FRs and architecture Decision 5 only.\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Read: 8, Grep: 5, Glob: 5, Bash: 1, Write: 1). 10 unique files, 11 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — dev-story (2026-04-03T11:41)\n\n- **Spinner approach**: Used `Date.now()` for spinner frame index — only advances on re-render, not on timer. Acceptable for current architecture but not smooth animation.\n- **Driver/cost row alignment**: Simple spacing rather than precise column-width calculations. May drift for long task names.\n- **No `ink-spinner` dependency**: Confirmed not installed. Used text-based braille frames.\n\nToken Report: 22 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 9, Edit: 10, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 9 unique files, 11 total reads. ink-workflow.tsx read 2x.\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — code-review (2026-04-03T11:49)\n\n- **HIGH: `formatElapsed` rounding bug** — `Math.round(seconds/60)` inflated displayed minutes (90s showed \"2m\"). Fixed with `Math.floor`.\n- **MEDIUM: Column alignment bug** — driver/cost rows used 5-space separators vs 3-col arrow width. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: Misleading comment** \"ref-based counter\" with no ref. Rewrote.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing tests** — added 3 tests (formatElapsed(0), fractional minutes boundary, loop-with-meta).\n- **LOW (not fixed): Spinner non-determinism** — `Date.now()` makes test assertions check \"any frame\" rather than specific one.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Column alignment fragile** — manual space counting; should use `string-width` for proper padding.\n- Coverage: 96.85% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor. 4576 tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 9 unique files, 9 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — verify (2026-04-03T11:55)\n\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** 1 `require-yield` in unrelated file. Not from this story.\n- **Verification gap:** AC 8 (NFR2 500ms) verified by code inspection (no artificial delays) rather than runtime timing. Strong but indirect evidence.\n- **Observation:** 29 workflow tests run in 39ms. Coverage 100% lines/statements, 94.82% branches.\n- Ran vitest twice (coverage + verbose) — could combine into one call.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 1, Grep: 5, Write: 1). 1 unique file. vitest run twice (could combine).\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 12)\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — create-story (2026-04-03T11:59)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Sprint status uses `epics-multi-framework.md` Epic 5 story definitions, not `epics-architecture-v3.md` which has a different 14-3 definition. Resolved by using multi-framework epic as source of truth.\n- **Risk:** `ink-renderer.test.tsx` already 881 lines. Adding more tests pushes it further. Test files appear exempt from 300-line limit but should be confirmed.\n- **Observation:** Engine does not currently pipe `driverName` to renderer's `update()` callback. Story intentionally makes the parameter optional so TUI layer is ready before engine wiring.\n\nToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 2, Read: 12, Grep: 9, Write: 1, Glob: 4). 14 unique files, 15 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — dev-story (2026-04-03T12:04)\n\n- **Problem:** Adding `RendererState` fields broke 4 existing tests — `makeState` helper missing new fields, `DriverCostSummary` crashed on `Object.entries(undefined)`.\n- **Workaround:** Added defensive `if (!driverCosts) return null` guard. Correct fix, not hacky.\n- **Code quality concern:** Renderer tests can only verify \"no crash\" behavior — `startRenderer` doesn't expose internal state. Component-level tests cover rendering assertions instead.\n- **Observation:** `noopHandle.update` needed typed params to match interface.\n\nToken Report: 22 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 6, Edit: 14, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1). 7 unique files, 8 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — code-review (2026-04-03T12:14)\n\n- **HIGH: Renderer driver tests had zero expect() assertions** — only verified no exceptions. Replaced with 6 App-level rendering tests with real assertions.\n- **HIGH: No test for DriverCostSummary in App layout.** Added App-level integration tests.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for driver name surviving args truncation (60-char limit).** Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Redundant two-stage null guard** in DriverCostSummary.\n- **Architecture: update() driverName not connected to workflow engine** — inert in production until future integration story.\n- Coverage: 96.86% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor. 4598 tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — verify (2026-04-03T12:18)\n\n- **Verification format mismatch:** First proof attempt used table format; rewrote to `## AC N:` + `**Verdict:**` format. Known issue.\n- **Warnings:** `No exec-plan found` and `Showboat not installed` — non-blocking.\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** 1 in `src/templates/otel-config.ts`, not from story.\n- **Verification gap:** AC 4 (multi-driver correctness) verified via unit tests only, no integration test with real multi-driver workflow.\n- ALL_PASS: 12/12 ACs verified.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 5, Write: 2). 2 unique files. `codeharness verify` run twice (format fix cycle).\n","numLines":302,"startLine":1,"totalLines":302}}}
