{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011J3DmFSQMTrw77gJqVm3ub","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 15.1: Plugin Pass-Through Configuration\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to specify plugins per task in workflow YAML and per agent in agent config,\n11\tso that gstack skills load in Claude Code sessions and omo agents load in OpenCode sessions without modifying the plugins themselves.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['gstack']` on a `claude-code` driver\n16\t   **When** the driver dispatches the task\n17\t   **Then** the claude-code driver passes `gstack` to the Agent SDK query options as a plugin entry\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['omo']` on an `opencode` driver\n21\t   **When** the driver dispatches the task\n22\t   **Then** the opencode driver passes `--plugin omo` as a CLI flag to the spawned process\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['some-plugin']` on a `codex` driver\n26\t   **When** the driver dispatches the task\n27\t   **Then** the codex driver logs a warning that plugins are unsupported and proceeds without passing plugin flags\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** an agent config YAML with a `plugins: ['gstack']` field\n31\t   **When** the agent is resolved via `agent-resolver.ts`\n32\t   **Then** `ResolvedAgent.plugins` contains `['gstack']`\n33\t   **And** the `agent.schema.json` validates the `plugins` field as an optional array of strings\n34\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n35\t\n36\t5. **Given** a workflow task with no `plugins` field but an agent with `plugins: ['gstack']`\n37\t   **When** the workflow engine builds `DispatchOpts`\n38\t   **Then** the agent's plugins are used as the effective plugins for the dispatch\n39\t   **And** the task's plugins field takes priority if both are specified (task overrides agent)\n40\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n41\t\n42\t6. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['task-plugin']` and an agent with `plugins: ['agent-plugin']`\n43\t   **When** the workflow engine builds `DispatchOpts`\n44\t   **Then** the task's `plugins: ['task-plugin']` is used (task-level overrides agent-level, no merging)\n45\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n46\t\n47\t7. **Given** an existing workflow YAML with no `plugins` field on any task and no `plugins` on any agent\n48\t   **When** `codeharness run` executes\n49\t   **Then** the engine dispatches with `plugins: undefined` and no plugin flags are passed to any driver\n50\t   **And** behavior is identical to before this change (backward compatible)\n51\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t8. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n54\t   **When** the build completes\n55\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** `npm run test:unit` is executed after all changes\n59\t   **When** the tests complete\n60\t   **Then** all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n61\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n62\t\n63\t10. **Given** no new file exceeds 300 lines\n64\t    **When** line count is checked for all modified/created files\n65\t    **Then** every source file stays under 300 lines\n66\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n67\t\n68\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n69\t\n70\t- [ ] Task 1 (AC: #4): Add `plugins` field to agent schema and resolver\n71\t  - [ ] In `src/schemas/agent.schema.json`, add `plugins` as an optional array of strings (same shape as workflow task plugins)\n72\t  - [ ] In `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts`, add `plugins?: string[]` to `ResolvedAgent` interface\n73\t  - [ ] Ensure agent YAML with `plugins: ['gstack']` resolves correctly\n74\t\n75\t- [ ] Task 2 (AC: #5, #6, #7): Wire agent-level plugins into workflow engine dispatch\n76\t  - [ ] In `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`, when building `DispatchOpts`, resolve plugins via: `task.plugins ?? agent.plugins ?? undefined`\n77\t  - [ ] Task-level plugins override agent-level (no merging) — if task specifies plugins, agent plugins are ignored\n78\t  - [ ] If neither task nor agent specifies plugins, `plugins` remains `undefined` (backward compatible)\n79\t\n80\t- [ ] Task 3 (AC: #1): Verify claude-code driver plugin pass-through\n81\t  - [ ] Confirm existing behavior: `ClaudeCodeDriver.dispatch()` already passes `opts.plugins` to `queryOptions.plugins` (line 185-186 of `claude-code.ts`)\n82\t  - [ ] Add/verify test in `claude-code-driver.test.ts` that gstack plugin is passed to SDK options\n83\t\n84\t- [ ] Task 4 (AC: #2): Verify opencode driver plugin pass-through\n85\t  - [ ] Confirm existing behavior: `OpenCodeDriver.dispatch()` already passes `opts.plugins` as `--plugin` flags (lines 228-230 of `opencode.ts`)\n86\t  - [ ] Add/verify test in `opencode-driver.test.ts` that omo plugin is passed as `--plugin omo` flag\n87\t\n88\t- [ ] Task 5 (AC: #3): Verify codex driver plugin warning\n89\t  - [ ] Confirm existing behavior: `CodexDriver.dispatch()` already warns and ignores plugins (lines 213-216 of `codex.ts`)\n90\t  - [ ] Add/verify test in `codex-driver.test.ts` that plugins trigger warning and are ignored\n91\t\n92\t- [ ] Task 6 (AC: #4, #5, #6): Write unit tests for agent-level plugins\n93\t  - [ ] Test: agent schema validates `plugins: ['gstack']` successfully\n94\t  - [ ] Test: agent schema validates agent without `plugins` field (backward compat)\n95\t  - [ ] Test: `ResolvedAgent` with plugins resolves correctly\n96\t  - [ ] Test: workflow engine uses task.plugins when both task and agent have plugins\n97\t  - [ ] Test: workflow engine falls back to agent.plugins when task has no plugins\n98\t  - [ ] Test: workflow engine uses undefined when neither task nor agent has plugins\n99\t\n100\t- [ ] Task 7 (AC: #8): Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n101\t- [ ] Task 8 (AC: #9): Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, zero regressions\n102\t- [ ] Task 9 (AC: #10): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n103\t\n104\t## Dev Notes\n105\t\n106\t### Architecture Compliance\n107\t\n108\tThis story implements Epic 6, Story 6.1 (mapped to sprint Epic 15, Story 15-1) \"Plugin Pass-Through Configuration\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n109\t- **FR21:** User can configure gstack skills to load within claude-code driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n110\t- **FR22:** User can configure omo agents to load within opencode driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n111\t- **FR23:** System can pass plugin-specific configuration to the driver's CLI invocation\n112\t- **NFR12:** Plugin ecosystem integration must not require modifications to the plugins themselves\n113\t\n114\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n115\t- **Decision 6 (Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through):** Declarative config in YAML. Drivers handle translation. No framework-specific knowledge leaks into the workflow engine.\n116\t\n117\t### What Already Exists (from previous epics)\n118\t\n119\t**Plugin pass-through is already implemented at the driver level.** The core plumbing exists:\n120\t\n121\t1. **Workflow schema** (`src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` line 96-100): `plugins` is already defined as optional `array[string]` on task definition\n122\t2. **Workflow parser** (`src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` lines 205-206): already parses `task.plugins` into `ResolvedTask.plugins`\n123\t3. **Workflow engine** (`src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` line 338): already spreads `task.plugins` into `DispatchOpts`\n124\t4. **ClaudeCodeDriver** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` lines 185-186): passes `opts.plugins` to Agent SDK `queryOptions.plugins`\n125\t5. **OpenCodeDriver** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` lines 228-230): passes `opts.plugins` as `--plugin` CLI flags\n126\t6. **CodexDriver** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts` lines 213-216): warns and ignores unsupported plugins\n127\t7. **DispatchOpts** (`src/lib/agents/types.ts` line 90): already has `plugins?: readonly string[]`\n128\t8. **DriverCapabilities** (`src/lib/agents/types.ts` lines 27-31): `supportsPlugins` flag exists on all drivers\n129\t9. **Existing tests**: All three drivers have plugin pass-through tests\n130\t\n131\t**What's missing (the actual work for this story):**\n132\t\n133\t1. **Agent-level plugin configuration** — `agent.schema.json` has no `plugins` field, `ResolvedAgent` interface has no `plugins` property\n134\t2. **Plugin resolution cascade** — The workflow engine only reads `task.plugins`, not `agent.plugins`. FR21/FR22 say \"via workflow or agent config\"\n135\t3. **Integration tests** for the combined task+agent plugin resolution\n136\t\n137\t### Plugin Resolution Cascade (New)\n138\t\n139\tLike model resolution (`task.model → agent.model → driver.defaultModel`), plugins should follow:\n140\t- **Task-level `plugins`** (highest priority) — overrides agent\n141\t- **Agent-level `plugins`** (fallback) — used when task has none\n142\t- **No plugins** (default) — nothing passed\n143\t\n144\tUnlike model resolution, plugins are NOT merged. Task-level completely replaces agent-level. Rationale: merging creates ambiguity about plugin ordering and potential conflicts. Override semantics are simpler and more predictable.\n145\t\n146\t### Data Flow\n147\t\n148\t```\n149\tagent YAML (plugins: ['gstack'])\n150\t     ↓\n151\tagent-resolver → ResolvedAgent { plugins: ['gstack'] }\n152\t     ↓\n153\tworkflow-engine → resolvePlugins(task, agent) → task.plugins ?? agent.plugins\n154\t     ↓\n155\tDispatchOpts { plugins: ['gstack'] }\n156\t     ↓\n157\tdriver.dispatch(opts) → framework-specific CLI flags\n158\t```\n159\t\n160\t### What NOT to Do\n161\t\n162\t- Do NOT modify any driver files (`claude-code.ts`, `codex.ts`, `opencode.ts`) — their plugin handling is already correct and tested\n163\t- Do NOT modify `DispatchOpts` or `DriverCapabilities` — they already support plugins\n164\t- Do NOT modify the workflow schema — `plugins` on tasks is already there\n165\t- Do NOT merge task and agent plugins — task overrides agent, period\n166\t- Do NOT add new npm dependencies\n167\t- Do NOT modify TUI components — this is a configuration story, not a display story\n168\t\n169\t### Line Budget Analysis\n170\t\n171\t| File | Current Lines | Estimated Change | Target |\n172\t|------|--------------|------------------|--------|\n173\t| `agent.schema.json` | 86 | +6 (plugins property) | ~92 |\n174\t| `agent-resolver.ts` | ~200 | +2 (plugins field) | ~202 |\n175\t| `workflow-engine.ts` | ~400 | +5 (plugin cascade) | ~405 |\n176\t| Tests (various) | — | +40-60 (new test cases) | within budget |\n177\t\n178\tAll source files stay well under 300 lines.\n179\t\n180\t### Testing Guidance\n181\t\n182\t- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n183\t- For agent schema tests: extend existing `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts` or schema validation tests\n184\t- For workflow engine plugin resolution: extend existing `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n185\t- For driver tests: the existing tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/claude-code-driver.test.ts`, `codex-driver.test.ts`, and `opencode-driver.test.ts` already cover plugin pass-through. Verify they still pass — no new driver tests needed unless gaps found.\n186\t- Pattern: follow the model resolution tests as a template for plugin resolution tests\n187\t\n188\t### Previous Story Intelligence (14-3)\n189\t\n190\t- Story 14-3 was a TUI-layer story extending activity components with driver names. Minimal overlap with this config story.\n191\t- Pattern from earlier stories: extend interfaces first (schema + types), then wire into engine, then write tests. Keep backward compatibility as the primary constraint.\n192\t- The test suite is large (4591+ tests). Add tests sparingly — focus on the new behavior (agent-level plugins, resolution cascade).\n193\t\n194\t### Git Intelligence\n195\t\n196\tLast commits:\n197\t- `8272ef0 feat: epic 14 complete`\n198\t- `e54c9b4 feat: story 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration`\n199\t\n200\tRecent pattern: stories that extend existing plumbing (type extensions → engine wiring → tests) complete cleanly in one pass.\n201\t\n202\t### References\n203\t\n204\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 6.1: Plugin Pass-Through Configuration]\n205\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 6: Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through]\n206\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — FR21, FR22, FR23, NFR12]\n207\t- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json — agent config schema, no plugins field yet]\n208\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — ResolvedAgent interface, no plugins property]\n209\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — line 338, task.plugins pass-through to DispatchOpts]\n210\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts — lines 185-186, SDK plugin pass-through]\n211\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts — lines 228-230, --plugin CLI flags]\n212\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts — lines 213-216, warn and ignore]\n213\t- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — DispatchOpts.plugins, DriverCapabilities.supportsPlugins]\n214\t\n215\t## Files to Change\n216\t\n217\t- `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — Add optional `plugins` field (array of strings)\n218\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — Add `plugins?: string[]` to `ResolvedAgent` interface\n219\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Resolve plugins via `task.plugins ?? agent.plugins ?? undefined` when building `DispatchOpts`\n220\t- `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts` — Add tests for agent-level plugin resolution\n221\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — Add tests for plugin cascade (task overrides agent, agent fallback, no plugins)\n222\t\n223\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n224\t## Verification Requirements\n225\t\n226\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration-proof.md)\n227\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n228\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n229\t\n230\t## Documentation Requirements\n231\t\n232\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n233\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration.md\n234\t\n235\t## Testing Requirements\n236\t\n237\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n238\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n239\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n240\t\n241\t## Dev Agent Record\n242\t\n243\t### Agent Model Used\n244\t\n245\t{{agent_model_name_version}}\n246\t\n247\t### Debug Log References\n248\t\n249\t### Completion Notes List\n250\t\n251\t### Change Log\n252\t\n253\t- 2026-04-03: Story created with 10 ACs covering FR21-FR23 and NFR12. Agent-level plugin config is the primary new work; driver-level pass-through already exists from Epics 10-12. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n254\t\n255\t### File List\n256\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49777568-67d3-419d-b985-1c272283fc99","uuid":"a8c46f36-e8b6-4b21-b240-dad15b473dca","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:27:48.355Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration.md","content":"# Story 15.1: Plugin Pass-Through Configuration\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a user,\nI want to specify plugins per task in workflow YAML and per agent in agent config,\nso that gstack skills load in Claude Code sessions and omo agents load in OpenCode sessions without modifying the plugins themselves.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['gstack']` on a `claude-code` driver\n   **When** the driver dispatches the task\n   **Then** the claude-code driver passes `gstack` to the Agent SDK query options as a plugin entry\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['omo']` on an `opencode` driver\n   **When** the driver dispatches the task\n   **Then** the opencode driver passes `--plugin omo` as a CLI flag to the spawned process\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['some-plugin']` on a `codex` driver\n   **When** the driver dispatches the task\n   **Then** the codex driver logs a warning that plugins are unsupported and proceeds without passing plugin flags\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** an agent config YAML with a `plugins: ['gstack']` field\n   **When** the agent is resolved via `agent-resolver.ts`\n   **Then** `ResolvedAgent.plugins` contains `['gstack']`\n   **And** the `agent.schema.json` validates the `plugins` field as an optional array of strings\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** a workflow task with no `plugins` field but an agent with `plugins: ['gstack']`\n   **When** the workflow engine builds `DispatchOpts`\n   **Then** the agent's plugins are used as the effective plugins for the dispatch\n   **And** the task's plugins field takes priority if both are specified (task overrides agent)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** a workflow task with `plugins: ['task-plugin']` and an agent with `plugins: ['agent-plugin']`\n   **When** the workflow engine builds `DispatchOpts`\n   **Then** the task's `plugins: ['task-plugin']` is used (task-level overrides agent-level, no merging)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** an existing workflow YAML with no `plugins` field on any task and no `plugins` on any agent\n   **When** `codeharness run` executes\n   **Then** the engine dispatches with `plugins: undefined` and no plugin flags are passed to any driver\n   **And** behavior is identical to before this change (backward compatible)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n8. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n   **When** the build completes\n   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n9. **Given** `npm run test:unit` is executed after all changes\n   **When** the tests complete\n   **Then** all existing tests pass with zero regressions\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n10. **Given** no new file exceeds 300 lines\n    **When** line count is checked for all modified/created files\n    **Then** every source file stays under 300 lines\n    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1 (AC: #4): Add `plugins` field to agent schema and resolver\n  - [ ] In `src/schemas/agent.schema.json`, add `plugins` as an optional array of strings (same shape as workflow task plugins)\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts`, add `plugins?: string[]` to `ResolvedAgent` interface\n  - [ ] Ensure agent YAML with `plugins: ['gstack']` resolves correctly\n\n- [ ] Task 2 (AC: #5, #6, #7): Wire agent-level plugins into workflow engine dispatch\n  - [ ] In `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts`, when building `DispatchOpts`, resolve plugins via: `task.plugins ?? agent.plugins ?? undefined`\n  - [ ] Task-level plugins override agent-level (no merging) — if task specifies plugins, agent plugins are ignored\n  - [ ] If neither task nor agent specifies plugins, `plugins` remains `undefined` (backward compatible)\n\n- [ ] Task 3 (AC: #1): Verify claude-code driver plugin pass-through\n  - [ ] Confirm existing behavior: `ClaudeCodeDriver.dispatch()` already passes `opts.plugins` to `queryOptions.plugins` (line 185-186 of `claude-code.ts`)\n  - [ ] Add/verify test in `claude-code-driver.test.ts` that gstack plugin is passed to SDK options\n\n- [ ] Task 4 (AC: #2): Verify opencode driver plugin pass-through\n  - [ ] Confirm existing behavior: `OpenCodeDriver.dispatch()` already passes `opts.plugins` as `--plugin` flags (lines 228-230 of `opencode.ts`)\n  - [ ] Add/verify test in `opencode-driver.test.ts` that omo plugin is passed as `--plugin omo` flag\n\n- [ ] Task 5 (AC: #3): Verify codex driver plugin warning\n  - [ ] Confirm existing behavior: `CodexDriver.dispatch()` already warns and ignores plugins (lines 213-216 of `codex.ts`)\n  - [ ] Add/verify test in `codex-driver.test.ts` that plugins trigger warning and are ignored\n\n- [ ] Task 6 (AC: #4, #5, #6): Write unit tests for agent-level plugins\n  - [ ] Test: agent schema validates `plugins: ['gstack']` successfully\n  - [ ] Test: agent schema validates agent without `plugins` field (backward compat)\n  - [ ] Test: `ResolvedAgent` with plugins resolves correctly\n  - [ ] Test: workflow engine uses task.plugins when both task and agent have plugins\n  - [ ] Test: workflow engine falls back to agent.plugins when task has no plugins\n  - [ ] Test: workflow engine uses undefined when neither task nor agent has plugins\n\n- [ ] Task 7 (AC: #8): Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n- [ ] Task 8 (AC: #9): Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, zero regressions\n- [ ] Task 9 (AC: #10): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Architecture Compliance\n\nThis story implements Epic 6, Story 6.1 (mapped to sprint Epic 15, Story 15-1) \"Plugin Pass-Through Configuration\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n- **FR21:** User can configure gstack skills to load within claude-code driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n- **FR22:** User can configure omo agents to load within opencode driver sessions via workflow or agent config\n- **FR23:** System can pass plugin-specific configuration to the driver's CLI invocation\n- **NFR12:** Plugin ecosystem integration must not require modifications to the plugins themselves\n\nKey architecture decisions honored:\n- **Decision 6 (Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through):** Declarative config in YAML. Drivers handle translation. No framework-specific knowledge leaks into the workflow engine.\n\n### What Already Exists (from previous epics)\n\n**Plugin pass-through is already implemented at the driver level.** The core plumbing exists:\n\n1. **Workflow schema** (`src/schemas/workflow.schema.json` line 96-100): `plugins` is already defined as optional `array[string]` on task definition\n2. **Workflow parser** (`src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` lines 205-206): already parses `task.plugins` into `ResolvedTask.plugins`\n3. **Workflow engine** (`src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` line 338): already spreads `task.plugins` into `DispatchOpts`\n4. **ClaudeCodeDriver** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts` lines 185-186): passes `opts.plugins` to Agent SDK `queryOptions.plugins`\n5. **OpenCodeDriver** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts` lines 228-230): passes `opts.plugins` as `--plugin` CLI flags\n6. **CodexDriver** (`src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts` lines 213-216): warns and ignores unsupported plugins\n7. **DispatchOpts** (`src/lib/agents/types.ts` line 90): already has `plugins?: readonly string[]`\n8. **DriverCapabilities** (`src/lib/agents/types.ts` lines 27-31): `supportsPlugins` flag exists on all drivers\n9. **Existing tests**: All three drivers have plugin pass-through tests\n\n**What's missing (the actual work for this story):**\n\n1. **Agent-level plugin configuration** — `agent.schema.json` has no `plugins` field, `ResolvedAgent` interface has no `plugins` property\n2. **Plugin resolution cascade** — The workflow engine only reads `task.plugins`, not `agent.plugins`. FR21/FR22 say \"via workflow or agent config\"\n3. **Integration tests** for the combined task+agent plugin resolution\n\n### Plugin Resolution Cascade (New)\n\nLike model resolution (`task.model → agent.model → driver.defaultModel`), plugins should follow:\n- **Task-level `plugins`** (highest priority) — overrides agent\n- **Agent-level `plugins`** (fallback) — used when task has none\n- **No plugins** (default) — nothing passed\n\nUnlike model resolution, plugins are NOT merged. Task-level completely replaces agent-level. Rationale: merging creates ambiguity about plugin ordering and potential conflicts. Override semantics are simpler and more predictable.\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nagent YAML (plugins: ['gstack'])\n     ↓\nagent-resolver → ResolvedAgent { plugins: ['gstack'] }\n     ↓\nworkflow-engine → resolvePlugins(task, agent) → task.plugins ?? agent.plugins\n     ↓\nDispatchOpts { plugins: ['gstack'] }\n     ↓\ndriver.dispatch(opts) → framework-specific CLI flags\n```\n\n### What NOT to Do\n\n- Do NOT modify any driver files (`claude-code.ts`, `codex.ts`, `opencode.ts`) — their plugin handling is already correct and tested\n- Do NOT modify `DispatchOpts` or `DriverCapabilities` — they already support plugins\n- Do NOT modify the workflow schema — `plugins` on tasks is already there\n- Do NOT merge task and agent plugins — task overrides agent, period\n- Do NOT add new npm dependencies\n- Do NOT modify TUI components — this is a configuration story, not a display story\n\n### Line Budget Analysis\n\n| File | Current Lines | Estimated Change | Target |\n|------|--------------|------------------|--------|\n| `agent.schema.json` | 86 | +6 (plugins property) | ~92 |\n| `agent-resolver.ts` | ~200 | +2 (plugins field) | ~202 |\n| `workflow-engine.ts` | ~400 | +5 (plugin cascade) | ~405 |\n| Tests (various) | — | +40-60 (new test cases) | within budget |\n\nAll source files stay well under 300 lines.\n\n### Testing Guidance\n\n- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n- For agent schema tests: extend existing `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts` or schema validation tests\n- For workflow engine plugin resolution: extend existing `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts`\n- For driver tests: the existing tests in `src/lib/agents/__tests__/claude-code-driver.test.ts`, `codex-driver.test.ts`, and `opencode-driver.test.ts` already cover plugin pass-through. Verify they still pass — no new driver tests needed unless gaps found.\n- Pattern: follow the model resolution tests as a template for plugin resolution tests\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (14-3)\n\n- Story 14-3 was a TUI-layer story extending activity components with driver names. Minimal overlap with this config story.\n- Pattern from earlier stories: extend interfaces first (schema + types), then wire into engine, then write tests. Keep backward compatibility as the primary constraint.\n- The test suite is large (4591+ tests). Add tests sparingly — focus on the new behavior (agent-level plugins, resolution cascade).\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nLast commits:\n- `8272ef0 feat: epic 14 complete`\n- `e54c9b4 feat: story 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration`\n\nRecent pattern: stories that extend existing plumbing (type extensions → engine wiring → tests) complete cleanly in one pass.\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 6.1: Plugin Pass-Through Configuration]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 6: Plugin Ecosystem Pass-Through]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md — FR21, FR22, FR23, NFR12]\n- [Source: src/schemas/agent.schema.json — agent config schema, no plugins field yet]\n- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — ResolvedAgent interface, no plugins property]\n- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — line 338, task.plugins pass-through to DispatchOpts]\n- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/claude-code.ts — lines 185-186, SDK plugin pass-through]\n- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/opencode.ts — lines 228-230, --plugin CLI flags]\n- [Source: src/lib/agents/drivers/codex.ts — lines 213-216, warn and ignore]\n- [Source: src/lib/agents/types.ts — DispatchOpts.plugins, DriverCapabilities.supportsPlugins]\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `src/schemas/agent.schema.json` — Add optional `plugins` field (array of strings)\n- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — Add `plugins?: string[]` to `ResolvedAgent` interface\n- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Resolve plugins via `task.plugins ?? agent.plugins ?? undefined` when building `DispatchOpts`\n- `src/lib/__tests__/agent-resolver.test.ts` — Add tests for agent-level plugin resolution\n- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — Add tests for plugin cascade (task overrides agent, agent fallback, no plugins)\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### Change Log\n\n- 2026-04-03: Story created with 10 ACs covering FR21-FR23 and NFR12. Agent-level plugin config is the primary new work; driver-level pass-through already exists from Epics 10-12. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n\n### File List\n","numLines":256,"startLine":1,"totalLines":256}}}
