{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M8TZAbsCVkfpYfFyzHKvi3","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"49777568-67d3-419d-b985-1c272283fc99","uuid":"4437410a-b4ac-423b-bbfa-61196a05b964","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:33:58.358Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"Token Report: 18 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 12, Glob: 6, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 14 unique files. No redundancy.","newString":"Token Report: 18 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 12, Glob: 6, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 14 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration — dev-story (2026-04-03T12:32)\n\nNo issues reported. Build passes, 4612 tests pass across all test files, zero regressions. 14 new tests added (10 agent-resolver, 4 workflow-engine).\n\nToken Report: 24 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 12, Edit: 7, Grep: 6, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 12 unique files. No redundancy.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 9)\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — create-story (2026-04-03T09:20)\n\n- **Ambiguity: OpenCode CLI output format.** Architecture doc acknowledges must be \"reverse-engineered from real CLI output.\" Fixtures will be plausible guesses.\n- **Ambiguity: OpenCode auth check command.** Used `opencode auth status` as guess. Low risk — health check gracefully handles command failure.\n- **No project-context.md found** — workflow references it but none exists. No impact.\n- **Risk: classifyError duplication.** Both CodexDriver and OpenCodeDriver have identical implementations. Intentional per architecture.\n\nToken Report: 16 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Grep: 4, Glob: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:25)\n\nNo issues reported. Build passes, 4478 tests pass across 166 test files, zero regressions.\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Bash: 4, Read: 11, Edit: 3, Write: 6, Glob: 2, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — code-review (2026-04-03T09:30)\n\n- **LOW: Dead fixture files.** test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt exist but tests use inline data. Dead artifacts.\n- **LOW: classifyError/parseLine duplication.** ~80 identical lines between codex.ts and opencode.ts. Intentional per architecture.\n- **LOW: console.debug for unparseable lines.** No structured logger. Shared pattern across drivers.\n- No HIGH or MEDIUM issues. 96.78% coverage. All 169 files above 80% floor.\n\nToken Report: 12 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 7, Edit: 1, Grep: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation — verify (2026-04-03T09:35)\n\n- **Stale AGENTS.md precondition:** `codeharness verify` fails due to stale AGENTS.md files for src/lib/agents/drivers module. Pre-existing documentation debt, not story-related.\n- **Test count discrepancy:** Story changelog claims 64 tests, actual count is 69. Minor — 69 is current state.\n- **Branch coverage 96.03%:** 4 uncovered branches at lines 149, 198, 306-307 (edge cases in parseLine result handling and error catch block).\n- ALL_PASS: 11/11 ACs verified with evidence.\n\nToken Report: 11 tool calls (Bash: 7, Read: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — create-story (2026-04-03T09:39)\n\n- **Multiple epics files with different 12-3 definitions.** Correct source is epics-multi-framework.md based on sprint-status context.\n- **Risk: 5-second timeout NFR6** requires careful mock design with fake timers to avoid real waits in tests.\n- All 9 ACs tagged test-provable. Small, well-scoped story (~100-150 lines prod, ~150-200 lines tests).\n\nToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 2, Read: 8, Grep: 7, Write: 1, Glob: 3, Skill: 1). 10 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — dev-story (2026-04-03T09:45)\n\n- **Workaround: optional timeoutMs parameter** added to `checkDriverHealth()` for testability (fake timers caused unhandled rejection warnings). Clean solution, not in original spec.\n- **Existing test impact:** Updated `healthCheck` mock in workflow-engine.test.ts to return valid `DriverHealth` object. Updated `mockGetDriver` call count assertion (+1 for health check).\n- **Code quality concern:** `setTimeout` in `checkDriverHealth` not cleared after `Promise.all` resolves — standard Promise.race behavior but could use cleanup.\n- Build passes (0 errors), 4488 tests pass across 167 files, zero regressions.\n\nToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1). 6 unique files, 10 total reads. workflow-engine.test.ts read 4x, workflow-engine.ts read 3x. One redundant npm run build call.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — code-review (2026-04-03T09:51)\n\n- **HIGH: Timer leak fixed.** `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()`. Added `clearTimeout`.\n- **MEDIUM: Timeout error inaccuracy fixed.** Was reporting ALL drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation).\n- **MEDIUM: Double mock invocation fixed.** Test called `checkDriverHealth` twice per assertion.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing test added.** \"timeout error reports only drivers that did not respond\".\n- **LOW (not fixed): `HealthResult` type** defined inline in function body rather than module scope. Cosmetic.\n- Coverage: 96.79% overall, all 169 files above 80% floor.\n\nToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 6, Edit: 4, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start — verify (2026-04-03T09:55)\n\n- **Proof format mismatch:** Verifier subagent generated `### AC N:` headers but parser expects `## AC N:`. Also needed `bash`/`output` code block pairs. Manually rewrote proof document.\n- **Stale AGENTS.md files:** Fixed src/lib/agents/AGENTS.md, src/lib/AGENTS.md, created src/lib/agents/drivers/AGENTS.md. Pre-existing debt from stories 12-1/12-2.\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** `require-yield` at workflow-engine.test.ts:154. Not from this story.\n- ALL_PASS: 9/9 ACs verified. `codeharness verify` passes.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 3 unique files. npm run test:unit run twice (verbose + summary).\n\n### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — create-story (2026-04-03T10:04)\n\n- **Ambiguity: contract directory parameter vs hardcoded path.** Architecture says `.codeharness/contracts/` but parameterized API chosen for testability.\n- **Ambiguity: error handling pattern.** Codebase uses both `Result<T>` and thrown errors. Chose thrown errors to match workflow engine convention.\n- **Observation:** `output_contract` field already exists in workflow schema for a different purpose (task-level schema config vs runtime contract files). Naming overlap noted in Dev Notes.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 5, Glob: 5, Grep: 3, Write: 1). 6 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — dev-story (2026-04-03T10:08)\n\nNo issues reported. 11/11 new tests pass, 4500 tests across 168 files, zero regressions.\n\nToken Report: 17 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Write: 3). 5 unique files, 6 total reads. One re-read for Edit mismatch.\n\n### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — code-review (2026-04-03T10:12)\n\n- **HIGH: Path traversal vulnerability fixed.** `taskName` with `../` could write outside `contractDir`. Added `assertSafeComponent` validation.\n- **HIGH: Empty input validation fixed.** Empty `taskName`/`storyId` produced nonsensical filenames.\n- **MEDIUM: JSON parse error handling added** for `readOutputContract` corrupted files.\n- **MEDIUM: Platform guard** for `chmodSync` test (Windows).\n- **LOW (not fixed): No runtime schema validation at write time** — by design per story spec.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Concurrent write race condition** — unlikely in sync code.\n- Coverage: 96.79% overall, all 170 files above 80% floor. +6 tests (4506 total).\n\nToken Report: 22 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 8, Edit: 5, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 9 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization — verify (2026-04-03T10:16)\n\n- **Lint errors (2):** `output-contract.ts` lines 59 and 84 had `preserve-caught-error` lint violations — re-thrown errors missing `cause`. Fixed post-verification.\n- **AGENTS.md staleness:** `codeharness verify` initially blocked by stale AGENTS.md. Fixed by running doc-health and updating.\n- ALL_PASS: 10/10 ACs verified. `codeharness verify` passes after AGENTS.md fix.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 4, Grep: 1, Write: 1). 4 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection — create-story (2026-04-03T10:23)\n\n- **Ambiguity: scope boundary with story 13-3.** Scoped this story to formatting and prompt-building only — actual workflow-level \"read previous contract then inject\" orchestration belongs to 13-3.\n- **Missing `appendSystemPrompt` in CLI drivers.** Codex and OpenCode drivers ignore `appendSystemPrompt` — validates design decision to inject via `prompt` field instead.\n- **All ACs are `test-provable`.** Correct — all functionality is pure formatting/string manipulation plus simple wiring change.\n\nToken Report: 24 tool calls (Read: 9, Grep: 7, Bash: 3, Glob: 4, Write: 1, Edit: 1). 12 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection — dev-story (2026-04-03T10:27)\n\n- **`previousOutputContract` parameter never called yet.** Story 13-3 will supply the actual contract from `readOutputContract()`. By design.\n- **No workflow-engine integration test for wiring.** Existing test infrastructure uses heavy mocking; unit tests on formatting functions cover the logic.\n\nToken Report: 13 tool calls (Read: 5, Edit: 9, Bash: 3, Grep: 1). 5 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection — code-review (2026-04-03T10:32)\n\n- **MEDIUM: `dispatchTask()` public API missing `previousOutputContract` parameter.** The internal `dispatchTaskWithResult()` accepted the parameter, but the public `dispatchTask()` didn't forward it, making the wiring dead code for story 13-3. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: No workflow engine integration test for contract injection (AC #10).** Fixed by adding vi.mock and 2 integration tests.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing boundary test for output truncation at exactly 2001 characters.** Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): No markdown sanitization in `formatContractAsPromptContext`.** By design.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `toFixed(2)` cost formatting shows `$0.00` for sub-cent costs.** Cosmetic.\n- Coverage: 96.8% overall, all 170 files above 80% floor.\n\nToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 6, Grep: 5, Glob: 2). workflow-engine.test.ts read 3x.\n\n### 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection — verify (2026-04-03T10:38)\n\n- **Lint error:** 1 pre-existing `require-yield` error in unrelated file — not from story 13-2.\n- **Verify format mismatch:** Initial proof used wrong format (`**Status:** PASS` instead of `**Verdict:** PASS`). Rewrote to match expected format.\n- **Verify warnings:** No exec-plan found and Showboat not installed — non-blocking.\n- ALL_PASS: 12/12 ACs verified.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 2, Grep: 4, Write: 1). 2 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution — create-story (2026-04-03T10:48)\n\n- **Risk: `changedFiles` extraction** depends on drivers emitting `tool-complete` events with parseable tool names (Write/Edit). Not all drivers may do this consistently.\n- **Risk: AC #7 crash recovery with contracts** implicitly covered by existing `isTaskCompleted` logic + atomic writes from 13-1 — test needs to simulate specific sequence carefully.\n- **Risk: `dispatchTask()` return type change** (Task 5) is breaking change to public signature — dev must update all call sites.\n- **Observation:** Capstone story for Epic 13. `previousOutputContract` was pre-wired in 13-2 for this story.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Read: 5, Grep: 5, Glob: 4, Bash: 1, Write: 1). 8 unique files. No redundancy.\n\n### 13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution — dev-story (2026-04-03T10:55)\n\nNo issues reported. Build passes, 4543 tests across 168 files, zero regressions. 16 new tests added.\n\nToken Report: 30 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 12, Edit: 16, Grep: 4). 5 unique files, 12 total reads. workflow-engine.test.ts read 7x (offset-based, necessary due to size).\n\n### 13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution — code-review (2026-04-03T11:02)\n\n- **MEDIUM: `changedFiles` not deduplicated** — same file path could appear multiple times. Fixed with `[...new Set()]`.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing 3-step sequential flow test** for AC #3. Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `dispatchTask()` public API is effectively dead code** internally — all internal call sites use `dispatchTaskWithResult()`. Backward compat retained.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Task 5 spec deviation** — story says change `dispatchTask()` return type but implementation kept old signature for compat.\n- Coverage: 96.82% overall, all 170 files above 80% floor. 4545 tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 27 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 16, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. workflow-engine.test.ts read 8x (size-limited).\n\n### 13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution — verify (2026-04-03T11:10)\n\n- **Proof format mismatch:** Proof had `**Verification tier:**` but parser expects `**Tier:**`. Fixed.\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** `require-yield` at workflow-engine.test.ts:164 — generator function from 13-3 tests, not a regression.\n- **Verification gap:** AC 7 (crash recovery + contract persistence) verified by code inspection rather than a dedicated combined test.\n- **Coverage not run by verifier** — `codeharness coverage` not invoked. Test count (4545) and prior code-review coverage (96.82%) provide confidence.\n- ALL_PASS: 10/10 ACs verified. `codeharness verify` passes (exit 0).\n\nToken Report: 17 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 4, Grep: 5, Write: 1). 4 unique files. `npm run lint` checked twice, `ls verification/` run twice (minor redundancy).\n\nToken Report: 27 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 16, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 8 unique files. workflow-engine.test.ts read 8x (size-limited).\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 10)\n\n### 14-1-workflowgraph-component — create-story (2026-04-03T11:14)\n\n- **No UX spec coverage for workflow graph.** UX design spec predates multi-framework PRD. All behavioral requirements from epics/architecture only.\n- **Spinner vs static indicator:** Architecture says \"cyan + spinner\" for active tasks, but codebase uses `◆`. Defaulted to `◆`, deferred spinner to 14-2.\n- **ink-testing-library availability unknown.** Dev notes instruct developer to check before writing tests.\n- **Sprint-status not updated by subagent** — orchestrator handled it.\n\nToken Report: 18 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 10, Glob: 5, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 12 unique files, 14 total reads. ink-components.tsx and ink-renderer.tsx read 2x each.\n\n### 14-1-workflowgraph-component — dev-story (2026-04-03T11:18)\n\n- **Loop iteration counting is a heuristic.** `loopIteration()` returns 0 or 1 — real iteration count requires engine-provided data wired in integration story.\n- **No color assertion in tests.** `ink-testing-library` `lastFrame()` strips ANSI. Tests verify symbols (checkmark, cross, diamond) as proxies.\n\nToken Report: 24 tool calls (Bash: 8, Read: 5, Edit: 14, Write: 2). 5 unique files, 6 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-1-workflowgraph-component — code-review (2026-04-03T11:25)\n\n- **HIGH: `loopIteration` dead code branches.** Simplified redundant/dead logic.\n- **HIGH: Separator width hard-capped at 50** instead of matching UI terminal width. Fixed to cap at 80.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for loop iteration=0.** Added 3 loop iteration tests.\n- **MEDIUM: `updateWorkflowState` untested in controller.** Added tests.\n- **LOW (not fixed): `currentTask` prop is dead code** — kept for API contract compatibility.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Nested `<Text>` inside `<Text>`** in loop rendering — valid Ink behavior.\n- Coverage: 96.83% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor.\n\nToken Report: 21 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 8 unique files, 9 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-1-workflowgraph-component — verify (2026-04-03T11:30)\n\n- 1 pre-existing lint error (`require-yield` in unrelated file) and 52 warnings. None from story 14-1.\n- `codeharness verify` warnings: \"Showboat not installed\" and \"No exec-plan found\" — non-blocking.\n- ALL_PASS: 8/8 ACs verified.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 10, Read: 2, Write: 1). 2 unique files. `npm run test:unit` run twice (pass/fail + verbose names).\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 11)\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — create-story (2026-04-03T11:36)\n\n- **No project-context.md found.** Workflow references it but none exists. Not a blocker.\n- **Config.yaml path mismatch.** Workflow expected `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`, actual is `_bmad/config.yaml`.\n- **Spinner dependency uncertainty.** Architecture says spinner, 14-1 chose static `◆`. Story instructs dev to check for ink-spinner first.\n- **No UX spec coverage.** All requirements from PRD FRs and architecture Decision 5 only.\n\nToken Report: 20 tool calls (Read: 8, Grep: 5, Glob: 5, Bash: 1, Write: 1). 10 unique files, 11 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — dev-story (2026-04-03T11:41)\n\n- **Spinner approach**: Used `Date.now()` for spinner frame index — only advances on re-render, not on timer. Acceptable for current architecture but not smooth animation.\n- **Driver/cost row alignment**: Simple spacing rather than precise column-width calculations. May drift for long task names.\n- **No `ink-spinner` dependency**: Confirmed not installed. Used text-based braille frames.\n\nToken Report: 22 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 9, Edit: 10, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 9 unique files, 11 total reads. ink-workflow.tsx read 2x.\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — code-review (2026-04-03T11:49)\n\n- **HIGH: `formatElapsed` rounding bug** — `Math.round(seconds/60)` inflated displayed minutes (90s showed \"2m\"). Fixed with `Math.floor`.\n- **MEDIUM: Column alignment bug** — driver/cost rows used 5-space separators vs 3-col arrow width. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: Misleading comment** \"ref-based counter\" with no ref. Rewrote.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing tests** — added 3 tests (formatElapsed(0), fractional minutes boundary, loop-with-meta).\n- **LOW (not fixed): Spinner non-determinism** — `Date.now()` makes test assertions check \"any frame\" rather than specific one.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Column alignment fragile** — manual space counting; should use `string-width` for proper padding.\n- Coverage: 96.85% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor. 4576 tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 6, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 9 unique files, 9 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-2-task-status-driver-labels — verify (2026-04-03T11:55)\n\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** 1 `require-yield` in unrelated file. Not from this story.\n- **Verification gap:** AC 8 (NFR2 500ms) verified by code inspection (no artificial delays) rather than runtime timing. Strong but indirect evidence.\n- **Observation:** 29 workflow tests run in 39ms. Coverage 100% lines/statements, 94.82% branches.\n- Ran vitest twice (coverage + verbose) — could combine into one call.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 1, Grep: 5, Write: 1). 1 unique file. vitest run twice (could combine).\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 12)\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — create-story (2026-04-03T11:59)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Sprint status uses `epics-multi-framework.md` Epic 5 story definitions, not `epics-architecture-v3.md` which has a different 14-3 definition. Resolved by using multi-framework epic as source of truth.\n- **Risk:** `ink-renderer.test.tsx` already 881 lines. Adding more tests pushes it further. Test files appear exempt from 300-line limit but should be confirmed.\n- **Observation:** Engine does not currently pipe `driverName` to renderer's `update()` callback. Story intentionally makes the parameter optional so TUI layer is ready before engine wiring.\n\nToken Report: 25 tool calls (Bash: 2, Read: 12, Grep: 9, Write: 1, Glob: 4). 14 unique files, 15 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — dev-story (2026-04-03T12:04)\n\n- **Problem:** Adding `RendererState` fields broke 4 existing tests — `makeState` helper missing new fields, `DriverCostSummary` crashed on `Object.entries(undefined)`.\n- **Workaround:** Added defensive `if (!driverCosts) return null` guard. Correct fix, not hacky.\n- **Code quality concern:** Renderer tests can only verify \"no crash\" behavior — `startRenderer` doesn't expose internal state. Component-level tests cover rendering assertions instead.\n- **Observation:** `noopHandle.update` needed typed params to match interface.\n\nToken Report: 22 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 6, Edit: 14, Grep: 2, Write: 1, Glob: 1). 7 unique files, 8 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — code-review (2026-04-03T12:14)\n\n- **HIGH: Renderer driver tests had zero expect() assertions** — only verified no exceptions. Replaced with 6 App-level rendering tests with real assertions.\n- **HIGH: No test for DriverCostSummary in App layout.** Added App-level integration tests.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for driver name surviving args truncation (60-char limit).** Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Redundant two-stage null guard** in DriverCostSummary.\n- **Architecture: update() driverName not connected to workflow engine** — inert in production until future integration story.\n- Coverage: 96.86% overall, all 171 files above 80% floor. 4598 tests pass.\n\nToken Report: 19 tool calls (Bash: 6, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 11 unique files, 12 total reads. No redundancy.\n\n### 14-3-activity-display-driver-integration — verify (2026-04-03T12:18)\n\n- **Verification format mismatch:** First proof attempt used table format; rewrote to `## AC N:` + `**Verdict:**` format. Known issue.\n- **Warnings:** `No exec-plan found` and `Showboat not installed` — non-blocking.\n- **Pre-existing lint error:** 1 in `src/templates/otel-config.ts`, not from story.\n- **Verification gap:** AC 4 (multi-driver correctness) verified via unit tests only, no integration test with real multi-driver workflow.\n- ALL_PASS: 12/12 ACs verified.\n\nToken Report: 14 tool calls (Bash: 9, Read: 2, Grep: 5, Write: 2). 2 unique files. `codeharness verify` run twice (format fix cycle).\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 13)\n\n### 15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration — create-story (2026-04-03T12:27)\n\n- **Epics numbering mismatch:** Epic 6 story 1 = sprint 15-1. Inherited from sprint planning renumbering.\n- **Risk: Agent SDK plugin API dependency.** SDK's `query()` `plugins` option behavior depends on SDK version — silent breakage risk.\n- **Observation:** Surprisingly small story. Bulk of plugin pass-through done in Epics 10-12. Remaining work: agent-level config path + resolution cascade (~15 lines prod, ~50 lines tests).\n- All 10 ACs tagged `test-provable`.\n\nToken Report: 18 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 12, Glob: 6, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 14 unique files. No redundancy.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":312,"oldLines":3,"newStart":312,"newLines":9,"lines":[" - All 10 ACs tagged `test-provable`."," "," Token Report: 18 tool calls (Bash: 3, Read: 12, Glob: 6, Grep: 4, Write: 1, Skill: 1). 14 unique files. No redundancy.","+","+### 15-1-plugin-pass-through-configuration — dev-story (2026-04-03T12:32)","+","+No issues reported. Build passes, 4612 tests pass across all test files, zero regressions. 14 new tests added (10 agent-resolver, 4 workflow-engine).","+","+Token Report: 24 tool calls (Bash: 5, Read: 12, Edit: 7, Grep: 6, Glob: 1, Skill: 1). 12 unique files. No redundancy."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
